        // ═══════════════ 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY ═══════════════
        heading("1. Executive Summary", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),
        body("The Designer\u2019s Compass is a suite of interactive web-based tools built for the Jacksonville Design Community to help UX/UI designers understand who they are, where they stand, and where they\u2019re headed in their careers. It connects three foundational concepts: designer archetypes (what kind of designer you are), a career ladder (where you are on the progression), and competency profiles (what skills define your current and aspirational level)."),
        body("Two artifacts have already been built and validated: the UX Designer Scorecard (a comprehensive self-assessment tool) and the Competency Radar (an archetype-vs-level visualization using D3 rose charts). This PRD defines the requirements for hardening these existing tools, building two additional artifacts (the Archetype Explorer and the Career Ladder Visualization), and ultimately combining all four into a single unified experience called The Designer\u2019s Compass."),
        body("The platform will serve as the centerpiece workshop activity for community meetups, a persistent career development resource for individual designers, and a talent intelligence tool for design leaders evaluating team composition and growth gaps."),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

