              ["Brand Worldbuilder", "#FFB800", "rgba(255,184,0,0.3)", "Cards, chart fills, highlights"],
              ["Interaction Crafter", "#A855F7", "rgba(168,85,247,0.3)", "Cards, chart fills, highlights"],
              ["Service Designer", "#34D399", "rgba(52,211,153,0.3)", "Cards, chart fills, highlights"],
              ["Research Strategist", "#F472B6", "rgba(244,114,182,0.3)", "Cards, chart fills, highlights"],
              ["Creative Technologist", "#FB923C", "rgba(251,146,60,0.3)", "Cards, chart fills, highlights"],
            ]).map(([arch, pri, glow, usage]) =>
              new TableRow({
                children: [
                  makeCell(arch, 2340, { run: { bold: true, size: 18 } }),
                  makeCell(pri, 2340, { run: { size: 18 } }),
                  makeCell(glow, 2340, { run: { size: 18 } }),
                  makeCell(usage, 2340, { run: { size: 18 } }),
                ],
              })
            ),
          ],
        }),
        spacer(100),
        body("Dark theme backgrounds: #08090E (deepest), #10121A (surface), #181B27 (elevated surface), #1E2133 (card). Light theme backgrounds: #F2F3F7 (deepest), #FFFFFF (surface), #F5F6FA (elevated), #FFFFFF (card). Border colors, text opacities, and accent color adjustments for light mode should follow the patterns established in the later session\u2019s toggle implementation."),

        heading("9.3 Component Patterns", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Shared interactive patterns across artifacts: rating dots (1\u20135 scale with fill animation and per-skill color), status buttons (multi-state toggles for asset tracking), card containers (border glow on interaction, numbered index, icon badge), section headers (numbered badge, title, subtitle), and the grain overlay (SVG noise texture at low opacity for premium feel). These should be extracted into shared React components."),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ 10. TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE ═══════════════
        heading("10. Technical Architecture", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),

        heading("10.1 Current Architecture", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Both existing artifacts are single self-contained HTML files with React 18, Babel Standalone, and (for the Radar) D3 loaded from CDNs. This architecture has the enormous advantage of zero-build portability: anyone can open the file locally or deploy to any static host without tooling. However, it has significant limitations for the unified dashboard: no code sharing between artifacts, no module system, runtime Babel transpilation adds latency, and the combined codebase of all four artifacts in one file would be unwieldy."),

        heading("10.2 Recommended Architecture for v2", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Migrate to a Vite + React build system. This was already prototyped in a previous session (the competency-radar.zip project). The recommended structure:"),
        bullet("Vite as the build tool (fast dev server, optimized production builds)"),
        bullet("React 18 with hooks (consistent with current implementation)"),
        bullet("D3 for the radar/rose chart (consistent with current implementation)"),
        bullet("CSS Modules or Tailwind for styling (replacing the mix of CSS custom properties and inline styles)"),
        bullet("Shared /src/data/ directory for canonical data models"),
        bullet("Shared /src/components/ directory for common UI components"),
        bullet("Each artifact as a route or standalone entry point"),
        bullet("Production build outputs static HTML/JS/CSS for any static host"),

        heading("10.3 Backward Compatibility", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("The build system should be configured to output both the unified dashboard (single-page app) and individual standalone HTML files for each artifact. This preserves the \u201Cdrop a file on any host\u201D workflow for workshops while enabling the richer integrated experience. The standalone builds can use Vite\u2019s library mode or a simple post-build script that inlines all JS/CSS into a single HTML file."),

        heading("10.4 No Server Required", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("The platform must remain entirely client-side. No databases, no authentication, no API calls. All data lives in the browser (React state, URL hash, or exported JSON files). This is a non-negotiable architectural constraint that reflects the community\u2019s values of openness and accessibility."),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ 11. INTEGRATION ═══════════════
        heading("11. Integration & Community Hooks", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),

        heading("11.1 Workshop Mode", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("A presentation-friendly mode (triggered by URL parameter or toggle) that increases font sizes, simplifies the interface to essential elements, and enables a facilitator view showing aggregate results. This supports the tool\u2019s primary use case as a meetup activity."),

        heading("11.2 Community Website Embed", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Each artifact should be embeddable as an iframe on the Jacksonville Design Community\u2019s website. The unified dashboard should also work as a standalone page linked from the community site."),

        heading("11.3 Slack Integration (Future)", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("A Slack bot command that posts a link to the Scorecard with a user\u2019s results pre-filled (from their saved JSON). This enables community members to share their archetype and score in the #introductions or #wins channels."),

        heading("11.4 Partnership Pitch Support", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Aggregated, anonymized community data (e.g., \u201COur 200 members break down as 28% Systems Architects, 22% Interaction Crafters...\u201D) that can be used in corporate partnership pitches to demonstrate the community\u2019s talent composition."),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ 12. ANALYTICS ═══════════════
        heading("12. Analytics & Success Metrics", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),
        body("Since the platform is server-free, analytics must be lightweight and privacy-respecting."),

        heading("12.1 Quantitative Metrics", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        numbered("Completion rate: Percentage of users who rate all competency sections (not just the first few).", "numbers3"),
        numbered("Share rate: Percentage of users who use the export/share feature.", "numbers3"),
        numbered("Cross-artifact flow: Percentage of users who navigate from Scorecard to Radar (the critical integration path).", "numbers3"),
        numbered("Return rate: Percentage of JSON imports (users returning to update their assessment).", "numbers3"),
        numbered("Workshop usage: Number of concurrent users during meetup events (measured by facilitator headcount, not tracking).", "numbers3"),

        heading("12.2 Qualitative Metrics", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        numbered("Post-workshop survey: \u201CDid the Scorecard help you identify a development area you hadn\u2019t considered?\u201D", "numbers4"),
        numbered("Archetype resonance: \u201CDoes the archetype description feel accurate to you?\u201D (1\u20135 scale)", "numbers4"),
        numbered("Conversation starter: \u201CDid you discuss your results with someone at the event?\u201D", "numbers4"),
        numbered("Community NPS: Overall community satisfaction trend correlated with tool adoption.", "numbers4"),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ 13. ACCESSIBILITY ═══════════════
        heading("13. Accessibility Requirements", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),
        body("As a tool built by designers for designers, accessibility is not optional. It is a reflection of professional values."),
        bullet("WCAG 2.1 AA compliance as the minimum standard."),
        bullet("All interactive elements must be keyboard-navigable with visible focus indicators."),
        bullet("The radar chart (SVG/Canvas) must have text alternatives: an accessible data table showing all scores alongside the visual chart."),
        bullet("Color is never the sole means of conveying information. Archetype identity should be reinforced with names, icons, and patterns in addition to color."),
        bullet("The rating dots must be operable via keyboard (arrow keys to adjust, Enter to confirm) and announced by screen readers."),
        bullet("Light and dark modes must both meet minimum contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)."),
        bullet("Touch targets on mobile must be at least 44\u00D744px."),
        bullet("Reduce motion preference (prefers-reduced-motion) must disable animations."),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ 14. RELEASE PLAN ═══════════════
        heading("14. Release Plan & Milestones", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),

        heading("14.1 Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1\u20134)", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Goal: Align the two existing artifacts on shared data models and fix critical gaps."),
        numbered("Extract shared data models (archetypes, levels, competencies) into canonical definitions.", "numbers5"),
        numbered("Align Scorecard archetype model to the 7-archetype system (SC-01).", "numbers5"),
        numbered("Add leadership competency section to Scorecard (SC-02).", "numbers5"),
        numbered("Implement personal overlay mode in the Radar (CR-01).", "numbers5"),
        numbered("Implement the Scorecard-to-Radar link (SC-08).", "numbers5"),
        numbered("Merge light/dark toggles into both canonical files (SC-05, CR-04).", "numbers5"),
        bodyRuns([{ text: "Exit criteria: ", bold: true }, { text: "A user can complete the Scorecard, click through to the Radar, and see their personal scores overlaid on their archetype benchmark. Both tools use the same archetype and competency definitions." }]),

        heading("14.2 Phase 2: New Artifacts (Weeks 5\u20138)", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Goal: Build the Archetype Explorer and Career Ladder Visualization."),
        bullet("Build the Archetype Explorer with cards and detail views (AE-01, AE-02)."),
        bullet("Build the Career Ladder Visualization with interactive nodes and the IC/Management fork (CL-01, CL-02)."),
        bullet("Implement the archetype quiz (AE-03)."),
        bullet("Add archetype overlay to the career ladder (CL-03)."),
        bodyRuns([{ text: "Exit criteria: ", bold: true }, { text: "All four artifacts exist as standalone pages with consistent data models and visual language." }]),

        heading("14.3 Phase 3: Unified Dashboard (Weeks 9\u201312)", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Goal: Integrate all four artifacts into the guided compass experience."),
        bullet("Set up Vite + React project structure with shared components."),
        bullet("Build the four-stage guided navigation (UD-01)."),
        bullet("Implement cross-stage data persistence (UD-02)."),
        bullet("Build the summary view (UD-03)."),
        bullet("Implement JSON export/import for the full assessment (SC-03)."),
        bullet("Implement share card generation (SC-04)."),
        bodyRuns([{ text: "Exit criteria: ", bold: true }, { text: "A user can move through all four stages, with data flowing between them, and export their complete results." }]),

        heading("14.4 Phase 4: Polish & Community Launch (Weeks 13\u201316)", HeadingLevel.HEADING_2),
        body("Goal: Accessibility audit, performance optimization, workshop testing, and public launch."),
        bullet("Accessibility audit and remediation (Section 13)."),
        bullet("Performance optimization (bundle size, first paint, animation frame rate)."),
        bullet("Workshop beta test at a community meetup."),
        bullet("Iterate based on beta feedback."),
        bullet("Deploy to community website."),
        bullet("Build standalone HTML exports for offline workshop use."),
        bodyRuns([{ text: "Exit criteria: ", bold: true }, { text: "The Designer\u2019s Compass is live on the Jacksonville Design Community website and has been used successfully at a meetup event." }]),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ 15. OPEN QUESTIONS ═══════════════
        heading("15. Open Questions & Decisions", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),

        new Table({
          width: { size: CONTENT_W, type: WidthType.DXA },
          columnWidths: [500, 4930, 2130, 1800],
          rows: [
            new TableRow({
              children: [
                makeHeaderCell("#", 500),
                makeHeaderCell("Question", 4930),
                makeHeaderCell("Options", 2130),
                makeHeaderCell("Status", 1800),
              ],
            }),
            ...([
              ["1", "Should archetypes be pure types or allow blended profiles?", "Pure only / Blended / Both", "Open"],
              ["2", "How closely should we follow Korn Ferry vs. our adapted model?", "Strict / Adapted / Inspired", "Leaning adapted"],
              ["3", "Should the career ladder be generic or customizable to company structures?", "Generic / Customizable", "Open"],
              ["4", "Is this a tool for individuals only, or also for managers building teams?", "Individual / Both", "Individual for v1"],
              ["5", "Should we migrate to Vite+React or stay with CDN-loaded single files?", "Vite / CDN / Hybrid", "Leaning hybrid"],
              ["6", "How do we reconcile the two competency frameworks (craft skills vs. leadership competencies)?", "Merge / Keep both / Replace", "Keep both (see 8.1.3)"],
              ["7", "Should workshop mode include a facilitator dashboard with live aggregate results?", "Yes / No / Future", "Open"],
              ["8", "What is the community\u2019s appetite for maintaining a codebase vs. static files?", "Active dev / Minimal", "Needs discussion"],
            ]).map(([num, q, opts, status]) =>
              new TableRow({
                children: [
                  makeCell(num, 500, { run: { bold: true, size: 18 }, align: AlignmentType.CENTER }),
                  makeCell(q, 4930, { run: { size: 18 } }),
                  makeCell(opts, 2130, { run: { size: 18, italics: true } }),
                  makeCell(status, 1800, { run: { size: 18, color: status === "Open" ? "CC6600" : "336699" } }),
                ],
              })
            ),
          ],
        }),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ APPENDIX A ═══════════════
        heading("Appendix A: Competency Score Matrix", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),
        body("Complete benchmark data for all 7 archetypes across 5 career levels. Each row represents the expected competency emphasis (1\u201310) for that archetype at that level. These scores represent relative emphasis, not absolute skill \u2014 the shape matters more than the individual numbers."),
        spacer(100),

        // Generate a compact table for each archetype
        ...Object.entries({
          "Experience Storyteller": [[2,1,2,5,7,5,1,2,4,5],[4,3,4,8,8,7,3,3,6,7],[5,4,6,9,9,8,5,5,7,8],[7,6,8,9,8,9,6,6,8,7],[9,7,9,10,8,10,7,7,9,7]],
          "Systems Architect": [[2,2,1,4,4,3,1,5,3,5],[5,5,4,7,6,5,3,8,4,7],[7,6,6,8,6,7,4,9,5,8],[8,8,8,8,6,8,6,10,5,8],[9,9,9,8,7,9,7,10,6,8]],
          "Brand Worldbuilder": [[2,2,2,6,4,5,1,2,6,4],[4,4,5,8,5,7,2,3,8,6],[6,5,7,9,6,8,4,4,9,7],[7,7,8,9,6,9,6,5,9,7],[9,8,9,10,7,10,7,6,9,7]],
          "Interaction Crafter": [[1,1,1,7,5,3,1,3,5,6],[3,3,3,9,7,5,2,5,7,8],[4,4,5,10,7,6,4,7,8,9],[6,5,7,10,7,7,6,8,8,9],[7,6,8,10,8,8,7,9,9,8]],
          "Service Designer": [[3,2,2,3,6,4,1,4,3,4],[5,5,5,5,8,6,3,7,4,6],[7,6,7,6,9,8,5,8,5,7],[8,8,8,6,9,9,7,9,6,7],[9,9,9,7,9,10,8,10,7,7]],
          "Research Strategist": [[3,2,2,2,7,4,1,3,4,3],[6,4,5,4,9,6,2,5,6,5],[7,6,7,5,9,8,4,7,7,6],[9,7,8,5,9,9,6,8,8,6],[10,8,9,6,10,10,7,9,9,6]],
          "Creative Technologist": [[1,1,1,6,3,2,1,3,7,6],[3,2,3,8,5,4,2,5,9,8],[4,3,5,9,5,6,3,6,9,9],[6,5,6,9,6,7,5,7,10,9],[7,6,7,9,7,8,6,8,10,9]],
        }).flatMap(([name, levels]) => {
          const levelNames = ["Junior", "Senior", "Staff", "Principal", "Fellow"];
          const comps = ["Strat", "Biz", "Stake", "Craft", "Empathy", "Comms", "Team", "Sys", "Innov", "Exec"];
          const colW = [1360, ...Array(10).fill(800)];
          return [
            bodyRuns([{ text: name, bold: true, size: 22 }]),
            new Table({
              width: { size: CONTENT_W, type: WidthType.DXA },
              columnWidths: colW,
              rows: [
                new TableRow({
                  children: [
                    makeHeaderCell("Level", 1360),
                    ...comps.map((c, i) => makeHeaderCell(c, 800)),
                  ],
                }),
                ...levels.map((row, li) =>
                  new TableRow({
                    children: [
                      makeCell(levelNames[li], 1360, { run: { bold: true, size: 16 }, shading: LIGHT_BG }),
                      ...row.map((v, i) => makeCell(String(v), 800, { run: { size: 16 }, align: AlignmentType.CENTER })),
                    ],
                  })
                ),
              ],
            }),
            spacer(120),
          ];
        }),

        new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

        // ═══════════════ APPENDIX B ═══════════════
        heading("Appendix B: Archetype Definitions", HeadingLevel.HEADING_1),
        body("Canonical descriptions for each designer archetype. These definitions should be used verbatim across all artifacts."),
        spacer(100),

        ...([
          { name: "The Experience Storyteller", color: "#FF3C64", habitat: "Disney, Pixar, theme parks, immersive entertainment, game studios", drive: "Emotion, narrative arc, delight, wonder", sig: "Feels like a journey \u2014 you experience it, not just view it", power: "Making people feel something specific at a specific moment" },
          { name: "The Systems Architect", color: "#00D4FF", habitat: "Enterprise SaaS, fintech, healthcare platforms, data infrastructure", drive: "Clarity from complexity, structure, scalability", sig: "Before/after transformations of dense information into navigable systems", power: "Making the incomprehensible usable" },
          { name: "The Brand Worldbuilder", color: "#FFB800", habitat: "Agencies, startups, luxury brands, media companies", drive: "Identity, cohesion, cultural resonance", sig: "Complete visual universes \u2014 logo to packaging to environmental design", power: "Making a brand feel inevitable" },
          { name: "The Interaction Crafter", color: "#A855F7", habitat: "Product studios, design systems teams, platform companies", drive: "Micro-moments, motion, precision of response", sig: "Prototypes and motion studies that make you say \u201Cthat feels right\u201D", power: "The invisible layer between intent and action" },
          { name: "The Service Designer", color: "#34D399", habitat: "Government, healthcare, consulting, operations-heavy organizations", drive: "End-to-end journeys, touchpoint orchestration, systemic change", sig: "Journey maps, blueprints, ecosystem diagrams \u2014 the big picture", power: "Seeing the whole system, not just the screen" },
          { name: "The Research Strategist", color: "#F472B6", habitat: "R&D labs, innovation teams, consulting firms, policy organizations", drive: "Evidence, insight, framing the right problem", sig: "Insight decks, frameworks, before/after impact narratives", power: "Changing what gets built before a single pixel is placed" },
          { name: "The Creative Technologist", color: "#FB923C", habitat: "Labs, studios, installations, experimental product teams", drive: "What\u2019s possible, merging code and craft", sig: "Things that make you ask \u201Chow did they do that?\u201D", power: "Bridging the gap between vision and technical reality" },
        ]).flatMap(a => [
          bodyRuns([{ text: a.name, bold: true, size: 26 }]),
          bodyRuns([{ text: "Natural habitat: ", bold: true }, { text: a.habitat }]),
          bodyRuns([{ text: "Core drive: ", bold: true }, { text: a.drive }]),
          bodyRuns([{ text: "Portfolio signature: ", bold: true }, { text: a.sig }]),
          bodyRuns([{ text: "Superpower: ", bold: true }, { text: a.power }]),
          spacer(140),
        ]),

        // Final footer
        spacer(300),
        divider(),
        new Paragraph({
          alignment: AlignmentType.CENTER,
          children: [new TextRun({ text: "End of Document", size: 18, font: "Arial", color: "999999", italics: true })],
        }),
      ],
    },
  ],
});

Packer.toBuffer(doc).then(buffer => {
  fs.writeFileSync("/mnt/user-data/outputs/designers-compass-prd.docx", buffer);
  console.log("PRD generated successfully.");
});
